# App Module Structure

Every app has modules. Each module in own folder under `app/`. All interfaces, enums, types in `types.ts` in same folder. Many `types.ts` allowed. No exported types in same file as `export class`; see [28-module-types-colocation.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/28-module-types-colocation.mdc). Module constants + top-level helpers for class → `constants.ts` and `utils.ts`; see [29-module-constants-utils-colocation.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/29-module-constants-utils-colocation.mdc). DB access in `*.repository.ts` only; services inject repositories — see [service-repository-layer.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/service-repository-layer.mdc).

## Structure

```
app/
  <module-name>/
    dto/
      <module-name>.dto.ts
    controllers/
      <module-name>.controller.ts
    <module-name>.module.ts
    <module-name>.repository.ts
    <module-name>.service.ts
    types.ts
    constants.ts
    utils.ts
```

## Rules

- **`*.repository.ts`** — DB access only; injects `PrismaService` (see [service-repository-layer.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/service-repository-layer.mdc))
- **`*.service.ts`** — Business logic; injects repository, not Prisma
- **`*.module.ts`** — In module folder (e.g. `search/search.module.ts`)
- **`*.dto.ts`** — In `dto/` subfolder (e.g. `search/dto/search.dto.ts`)
- **Controllers** — In `controllers/` (e.g. `search/controllers/search.controller.ts`)
- **Enums, types, interfaces** — In `types.ts` at module root
- **Module constants** — In `constants.ts` at module root (URLs, limits, literals; not env parsing)
- **Helper functions** — In `utils.ts` at module root (pure helpers for main class)

## Example

```
app/
  search/
    dto/
      search.dto.ts
    controllers/
      search.controller.ts
    search.module.ts
    search.repository.ts
    search.service.ts
    types.ts
    constants.ts
    utils.ts
```

## Imports

```typescript
// In search.controller.ts
import { SearchDto } from '../dto/search.dto';
import { SearchResult } from '../types';
```
